INSERT INTO `services` VALUES (1, 1, 2, '{\"en\":\"Dialysis Centre\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">A safe, luxurious and stress-free destination for kidney dialysis patients<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">For those suffering from chronic kidney failure the idea of visiting the beautiful island of Bali would have once been impossible.&nbsp;Today the concern of travel and health to the \\u201cIsland of the Gods\\u201d is no longer a matter in question for kidney patients booking their treatments at BIMC Hospital Nusa Dua.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Renal patients arriving to Bali are provided with the unique opportunity to experience Asia\\u2019s most popular island destination and its distinctive culture, colorful traditions and spectacular outdoors while being in close and convenient proximity to a five-star, Australian standard Dialysis Centre.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Out patients often chose to stay at any one of the upscale resorts in Nusa Dua, from quick getaways to extended holidays. The facility caters to the specific needs of individuals needing dialysis maintenance all in an aesthetic, spa-style-inspired environment ensuring hemodialysis treatment is performed with the highest comfort in serene surroundings.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">The BIMC Hospital Dialysis Centre follows the same stringent infection prevention and quality control protocols as dialysis units in Australia. And patients enjoy one-to-one nursing care and daily visits from our doctors and renal specialists all of whom speak fluent English.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Dialysis Centre open on Monday to Saturday, two sessions in a day. For an appointment, please contact our reception staff at&nbsp;<a class=\\\"opnctrl\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/bimcbali.com\\/bimc-siloam-nusa-dua\\/dialysis-centre#contactform\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out 0s; color: rgb(0, 97, 170);\\\">dialysiscentre@bimcbali.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}', '[]', 'service/i0B25VYBkjr7PT7Pd2Luf6P0I1RM4hrh681Y0RUm.jpg', 'asdadfa', NULL, '2021-01-08 04:57:46', '2021-01-09 04:29:53');
INSERT INTO `services` VALUES (2, 1, 2, '{\"en\":\"About Bariatric Surgery\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Commonly referred to as weight loss surgery, bariatric surgery is one of the few weight loss treatments that have a history of proven results. The term bariatric surgery refers to any surgical procedure on the stomach or intestines to induce weight loss. There are 4 different main types of bariatric surgery :<\\/p><ul style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Gastric Bypass Surgery<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Laparoscopic Banding<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Sleeve Gastrectomy (more commonly referred to as the Gastric Sleeve)<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Biliopancreatic Diversion<\\/li><\\/ul><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\">Laparoscopic bariatric surgery<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Laparoscopic weight-loss surgery involves making five half-inch incisions and performing the operation by observation through a small camera called the laparoscope. The entire operation is performed \\u201cinside\\u201d the abdomen after gas has been inserted to expand the abdomen and create a working space.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Advantages of the laparoscopic approach include less post-operative pain, a shorter hospital stay, faster return to work and improved appearance. Recovery time also is shorter, absent any operative complications.<\\/p><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\">Gastric Sleeve Surgery<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">What is gastric sleeve, and is it superior compared to other types of bariatric surgery?<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">Sleeve Gastrectomy (more commonly referred to as the Gastric Sleeve) is a procedure in which about 85% of the stomach is removed, leaving 15% of the original capacity which is shaped like a sleeve. The medical community is embracing this operation as an alternative to the band and bypass procedures because the results and the risks are in the middle. There is excellent midterm scientific data from the past five-plus years to prove the effectiveness of the sleeve, with results almost comparable to the bypass yet with a lower risk profile. Sometimes it is superior compared to other types of bariatric surgery.<\\/p><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\">Who is a good candidate for bariatric surgery?<\\/h2><ol style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Be over the age of 18<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Demonstrate that all appropriate and available non-surgical measures have been adequately tried but have failed to maintain weight loss<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Have a genuine desire to overcome your obesity problems and demonstrate full commitment to finally getting your weight under control<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Have a Body Mass Index (BMI) of greater than 40, or a BMI of &gt;35 accompanied by other issues related to health (co-morbidities). These co-morbidities include diabetes, high blood pressure, coronary artery disease, obstructive sleep apnea, osteoarthritis, hyperlipidemia, etc.<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Be mobile, medically stable, and have an actively involved and supportive primary care physician.<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Have a stable psychological status with adequate social support system to help them through<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">the course of surgery and the postoperative period.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}', '[]', 'service/6ndO1eCK0IXiIT5Rh8ElyyLsHBFO2sUwq02cze3V.jpg', 'asdfadf', NULL, '2021-01-08 04:58:20', '2021-01-09 04:30:19');
INSERT INTO `services` VALUES (3, 1, 2, '{\"en\":\"Frequent Asked Questions\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"outline: 0px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-transform: none;\\\">What you need to know before undergo bariatric surgery<\\/p><ol style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">What can I expect when I first visit the hospital?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">You will have a thorough history taken at the time of your visit, and as a candidate for weight loss surgery you can expect to go through a series of consultations with our multidisciplinary team that consists of a digestive surgeon, an anesthesiologist, a clinical nutrition specialist, an internal medicine specialist.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Please make sure to bring any pertinent medical information and tests results from other physicians<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Since the clinical nutrition specialist will evaluate your dietary habits, and discuss healthy lifestyle changes before and after surgery, it is also a good idea to bring a list of everything you have eaten and their amounts in the two days prior to your appointment.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Your tests results, as well as your medical and dietary history, will be reviewed by the surgeon and any potential concerns will be discussed. The surgeon will then review with you the surgical procedures and potential risks of surgery as they pertain to your individual case.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"2\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">How do you determine which bariatric operation is best for a patient?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">The type of surgery that\\u2019s best for you will be determined by a team looking out for your best interest \\u2013 not the surgeon\\u2019s best interest or the hospital\\u2019s best interest. Our team considers each patient individually, taking into account the patient\\u2019s physical condition and ability to exercise, dietary habits, lifestyle, emotional concerns, etc. The team guides each patient into making an informed decision and provides individualized long-term care after an operation is complete.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"3\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Will I need any preoperative tests?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">To ensure the best possible outcome, we\\u2019ll administer specific blood tests, a chest x-ray, and an electrocardiogram (EKG). We\\u2019ll also test you for a bacteria that causes ulcers (known as H. pylori) and for gall stones. In some cases, we may also require a sleep study (for sleep apnea) or a psychological evaluation.<\\/p><\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">What are the risks of weight loss surgery?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">The risk of death associated with weight loss surgery is extremely low \\u2014 less than 0.5%. Risks, as all abdominal operations carry, may include:<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none;\\\"><ol style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1.5em; margin-left: 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: upper-alpha; display: inline-block;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none;\\\"><ol style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1.5em; margin-left: 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: lower-alpha; display: inline-block;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Bleeding<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Infection of the incision and abdomen<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Potential problems with the heart and\\/or lungs, including blood clots<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Obstruction (blockage) of the intestine caused by adhesions (scar tissue) or internal hernia<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Hernia through the incision or inside abdomen<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Rejection of suture material<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">The risks associated with general anesthesia; anesthesia risks are not significantly greater in most<\\/li><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">morbidly obese patients than in normal weight patients<\\/li><\\/ol><\\/li><\\/ol><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"5\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Will I be asked to stop smoking? Why ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Patients are highly encouraged to stop smoking at least three months before surgery. Smoking increases the risk of lung problems after surgery, can reduce the rate of healing, increases rates of infection, and interferes with blood supply to the healing tissues.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"6\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Recovery, How long will I be in the hospital ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">The average surgical time for gastric bypass is about 2 hours and sleeve gastrectomy is about 1-2 hours. Almost all our patients can walk a few hours after surgery. They start to have liquids the day after surgery. The majority (more than 95%) of patients only stay in the hospital for one night or two nights, unless a complication develops.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"7\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">How many follow-up visits are necessary after surgery ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Typically, you\\u2019ll attend four to six follow-up meetings during your first post-surgery year. Then visits are scheduled at six to twelve month intervals for an indefinite period of time. The operating surgeon and nutritionist will meet together with you during each follow-up visit.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Vitamin and mineral levels as well as protein intake are checked at regular intervals. After the first year, annual checkup visits are recommended for all patients.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"8\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">When can I return to normal activity ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">After surgery, most patients return to work after two to four weeks. Some may be able to work from home as early as one week after surgery. Any pain related to the surgery should go away after 7-10 days or so.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Because of the significantly reduced calorie intake, many patients have low energy for 1-2 weeks after surgery. However, most patients gain their energy back once they start to have soft food.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"9\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Can I get pregnant after bariatric surgery ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Yes! Most women are much more fertile after surgery, even with moderate pre-op weight loss. However, most surgeons recommend waiting 12-18 months after surgery before getting pregnant.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"10\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Will I lose my hair ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Some hair loss is common between 3 and 6 months following surgery, but it is temporary. Adequate intake of protein, vitamins and minerals will help to ensure hair re-growth, and avoid longer term thinning.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"11\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">When can I start exercising ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Right away! You should get out of bed and start walking as soon as possible after surgery.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Since walking greatly accelerates weight loss, specifically fat loss, we recommend walking 30 minutes per day to start, and increasing the amount of time to 45 minutes to one hour to maintain lost weight. The key is to start slow and listen to your body.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Avoid lifting heavy objects for the first 6 weeks. If you swim, your wounds need to be healed over before you get back in the water.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"12\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">How soon can I drive after surgery ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">You should not drive until you can move quickly and alertly and are no longer taking medications associated with your surgery. Usually this takes about one to two weeks.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"13\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Life After Surgery, What kind of weight loss can I expect ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">The results from gastric sleeve vary from patient to patient but most can expect to lose 1 to 1 \\u00bd kilograms per week until the normal weight range is reached. Most gastric bypass patients experience fairly rapid weight loss for three to six months after surgery. Weight loss slows but generally continues for 12 to 18 months after surgery.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Results vary from patient to patient, with the best results coming from those who are committed to lifestyle change. After 18 months, it is critical to adhere to the low-fat, low-sugar diet and exercise recommendations to maintain your weight loss. The most important concept for patients to remember is that these operations only help you comply with your diet. Success depends on the individual, and each individual has a different goal.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"14\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Does weight loss surgery guarantee permanent weight loss ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">No. A small percentage of patients will regain a substantial portion of the weight that is lost. This is occurs primarily when the patient does not follow the dietary guidelines in the months and years following the procedure.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"15\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Do I have to take vitamins and minerals after surgery ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Yes. we recommend that you take a daily multivitamin supplement containing the minerals necessary for good health. These should be taken for life. You will also need to have at least yearly lab checks.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"16\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Do I have to change my diet and exercise after surgery ?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Immediately after surgery, your doctor will provide you with special dietary guidelines. You will need to follow these guidelines closely. Allowing time for proper healing of your new stomach pouch is necessary and important. Eating soft sweets, such as chocolates, ice creams, or drinks\\/liquids high in calories can cause poor weight loss or weight gain.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol><ol start=\\\"17\\\" style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-right: 1em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; display: inline-block; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); text-transform: none;\\\"><li style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 5px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><h2 style=\\\"outline: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 5px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Will I need to have plastic surgery?<\\/h2><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">You will have a lot of change between 6 and 18 months after surgery. Your individual appearance depends upon several things, including how much weight you lose, your age, your genetics and whether or not you exercise or smoke. Generally, loose skin is well-hidden by clothing. Many patients wear compression garments to help with appearance.<\\/p><p style=\\\"outline: 0px;\\\">Some patients will choose to have plastic surgery to remove excess skin. Most surgeons recommend waiting at least 18 months, but you can be evaluated before that.<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ol>\"}', '[]', 'service/htTm14CxV4elSf44laxkQOS4q9GY8OCXz4p9JHYh.jpg', 'frequent-asked-questions', NULL, '2021-01-08 05:00:30', '2021-01-09 04:30:28');
